tag.value: Esri archive imagery that may be clearer and more accurate than the default layer.

It contains an orthorectified raster mosaic of the Capital District of Bogot, the Cerros Orientales and part of the rural area of Bogot of the localities of Ciudad Bolvar and Usme, corresponding to 75,000 hectares. It has 4 bands of the electromagnetic spectrum: Red, Green, Blue and Near Infrared, allowing to create a false color for forestry applications.
